{"type":"message","id":"157c7ee6","parentId":"b7b3f4df","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:32:08.702Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cpgg5za63xyb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 012815\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- The next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLooking at the logs directory, I need to find the pulse log files and implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nFrom the recent observation, the last pulse was at `pulse_2026-03-24 012614.md`. Let me check what pulse logs exist and implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier script that analyzes the pulse logs\r\n2. Or create the experiment documentation/plan\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available and make a concrete move forward on the TIC experiment. I'll implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLooking at the directory listing, I can see:\r\n- logs/ directory exists\r\n- research/ directory exists\r\n\r\nI should implement the TIC classifier. Let me create a Python script that will:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extract features (invariant vs variant patterns)\r\n3. Classify content\r\n4. Test next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The pulse logs exist but no TIC classifier is yet implemented to test the >70% invariant classification and >60% next-pulse prediction criteria.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that loads recent pulse logs, extracts temporal invariance features, classifies invariant vs variant content, and predicts next pulse content from invariants. This directly advances the Phase 1 TIC Experiment goal.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: \"\"\"\r\nTIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_LOGS_FOR_EXPERIMENT = 5\r\n\r\nclass TICIClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Temporal Invariance Content Item Classifier\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    INVARIANT_MARKERS = [\r\n        r\"Phase \\d\",           # Phase progressions\r\n        r\"Goal:\",              # Stable goals\r\n        r\"Completed\",          # Finished items\r\n        r\"Active\",             # Active status\r\n        r\"research/\",          # File paths (stable references)\r\n        r\"λ=\",                 # Parameters\r\n        r\"architecture\",      # Core concepts\r\n        r\"compression\",       # Core concepts\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    VARIANT_MARKERS = [\r\n        r\"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\", # Timestamps\r\n        r\"Last updated\",\r\n        r\"Recent:\",           # Recent observations\r\n        r\"Pending:\",          # Dynamic state\r\n        r\"Deferred\",\r\n        r\"pulse_\\d+\",         # Pulse-specific IDs\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.logs = []\r\n        self.invariant_features = Counter()\r\n        self.variant_features = Counter()\r\n        \r\n    def load_logs(self, n_recent=20):\r\n        \"\"\"Load n most recent pulse logs\"\"\"\r\n        log_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)\r\n        log_files = log_files[:n_recent]\r\n        \r\n        for f in log_files:\r\n            with open(f, 'r') as fh:\r\n                self.logs.append({\r\n                    'path': str(f),\r\n                    'content': fh.read()\r\n                })\r\n        \r\n        print(f\"Loaded {len(self.logs)} pulse logs\")\r\n        return len(self.logs) >= MIN_LOGS_FOR_EXPERIMENT\r\n    \r\n    def classify_line(self, line):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify a single line as invariant or variant\"\"\"\r\n        inv_score = 0\r\n        var_score = 0\r\n        \r\n        for pattern in self.INVARIANT_MARKERS:\r\n            if re.search(pattern, line, re.IGNORECASE):\r\n                inv_score += 1\r\n                \r\n        for pattern in self.VARIANT_MARKERS:\r\n            if re.search(pattern, line, re.IGNORECASE):\r\n                var_score += 1\r\n        \r\n        if inv_score > var_score:\r\n            return 'invariant'\r\n        elif var_score > inv_score:\r\n            return 'variant'\r\n        return 'neutral'\r\n    \r\n    def classify_log(self, log_content):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify entire log content\"\"\"\r\n        lines = log_content.split('\\n')\r\n        classification = {'invariant': 0, 'variant': 0, 'neutral': 0}\r\n        \r\n        for line in lines:\r\n            cls = self.classify_line(line)\r\n            classification[cls] += 1\r\n        \r\n        total = sum(classification.values())\r\n        if total == 0:\r\n            return {'invariant': 0.0, 'variant': 0.0}\r\n        \r\n        return {\r\n            'invariant': classification['invariant'] / total,\r\n            'variant': classification['variant'] / total\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def run_classification_experiment(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Run invariant/variant classification on all logs\"\"\"\r\n        results = []\r\n        for log in self.logs:\r\n            classification = self.classify_log(log['content'])\r\n            results.append({\r\n                'log': log['path'],\r\n                'invariant_ratio': classification['invariant'],\r\n                'variant_ratio': classification['variant']\r\n            })\r\n        \r\n        # Calculate overall accuracy (using majority classification per log)\r\n        correct = sum(1 for r in results if \r\n            (r['invariant_ratio'] > r['variant_ratio'] and 'Active' in open\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:28:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330328699}}
